The Department of State Services has arrested veteran journalist, author and activist, Dr. Chido Onumah. Onumah was reportedly arrested at the Abuja airport on Sunday evening when he returned to Nigeria from Spain where he recently bagged a doctorate in communication studies. He arrived via a Lufthansa airline and was waiting for his luggage at about 5:00 p.m. when SSS officials accosted him, an associate who was at the airport to receive him told online medium, Premium Times. He was believed to have been taken to DSS headquarters in Abuja.